# Azure Pricing & Cost Management (AZ-900)

## 💰 Pricing Models

### 1. Consumption-based (Pay-as-you-go)

* Pay only for what you use
* No upfront costs
* Scalable and flexible
* Default model in Azure

👉 Cloud = **OpEx (Operational Expenditure)**

---

### 2. Reserved Pricing (Reservations)

* 1 or 3 year commitment
* Lower cost compared to pay-as-you-go
* Best for predictable workloads

👉 Trade flexibility → for cost savings

---

### 3. Spot Pricing

* Very low cost
* Can be interrupted anytime

👉 Only for non-critical workloads

---

## 📊 Cost Management Tools

### Azure Pricing Calculator

* Estimate costs before deployment
* Plan architecture financially

👉 Use case:

* "How much will my solution cost?"

---

### Azure Cost Management + Billing

* Monitor and analyze usage
* Track spending
* Identify cost optimization opportunities

---

### Budgets

* Set spending limits
* Get alerts when thresholds are reached

👉 Important:

* Budgets do NOT automatically stop resources

---

## 📉 Cost Optimization Strategies

* Use **Reservations** for long-term workloads
* Use **Spot VMs** for non-critical jobs
* Stop/deallocate unused resources
* Right-size resources (avoid overprovisioning)

---

## 🧾 Key Concepts for Exam

* Cloud = **OpEx**, not CapEx
* Pay-as-you-go is default
* Reservations reduce cost
* Spot = cheapest but unreliable
* Budgets = alerts only (no automatic shutdown)

---

